メソッドの概要
 long getBlanks()
          The total net blank lines in this language across all projects on Ohloh.
 String getCategory()
          Either code, markup, or build, which indicates that the language
is either a “standard” programming language, a document markup language
such as XML, or a build script such as a makefile.
 long getCode()
          The total net lines of code, excluding comments and blank lines,
written in this language across all projects on Ohloh.
 float getCommentRatio()
          A precomputed floating-point value for the percent of lines
in this language that are comments, across all projects on Ohloh.
 long getComments()
          The total net comment lines written in this language across
all projects on Ohloh.
 long getCommits()
          The total number of commits on Ohloh which include
at least one line in this language.
 int getContributors()
          The total number of contributors on Ohloh who have written
at least one line of code in this language that still exists today.
 int getId()
          The unique ID of the language.
 String getName()
          A short, unique name for the language.
 String getNiceName()
          A human-friendly name for the language.
 int getProjects()
          The total number of Projects on Ohloh which currently include
at least one line in this language.
